The paper discusses success in science, specifically in the areas of peer review, citation, and new discoveries. These areas are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including social networks (cs.SI), digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cryptography (cs.CR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, given the focus on publication and recognition, we believe that cs.SI and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.CR, and cs.AI.
